- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses fragments of first-order logic over words, which can be characterized in terms of finite monoids.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses mathematical structures such as monoids and omega-terms.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the complexity of fragments of first-order logic and their satisfiability.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the least likely category as the paper does not explicitly discuss machine learning, but it does use mathematical tools that are relevant to the field.
